ags":[],"url":"/"},"2":{"id":"/-0","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/","content":"First-party product analytics ingress for ClickHouse."},"3":{"id":"/-1","page_id":"/","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/#why-build-this","content":"Why Build This"},"4":{"id":"/-2","page_id":"/","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/#architecture","content":"Architecture"},"5":{"id":"/-3","page_id":"/","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/#start","content":"Start"},"6":{"id":"/-4","page_id":"/","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/#operate","content":"Operate"},"7":{"id":"/-5","page_id":"/","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/#deployment","content":"Deployment"},"8":{"id":"/-6","page_id":"/","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/#reference","content":"Reference"},"9":{"id":"/-7","page_id":"/","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/#project","content":"Project"},"10":{"id":"/-8","page_id":"/","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/#quick-start","content":"Quick Start"},"11":{"id":"/-9","page_id":"/","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/#minimal-browser-example","content":"Minimal Browser Example"},"12":{"id":"/-10","page_id":"/","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/#minimal-backend-example","content":"Minimal Backend Example"},"13":{"id":"/-11","page_id":"/","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/#scope","content":"Scope"},"14":{"id":"/-12","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/","content":"ClickHouse Product Analytics is a first-party product analytics ingress layer for ClickHouse. It captures browser and backend product events, validates and normalizes them through one HTTP service, and writes query-ready events, people, identity links, and sessions into ClickHouse."},"15":{"id":"/-13","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/","content":"The project intentionally owns only the first mile of product analytics: event capture, identity stitching, and warehouse-native storage. It does not include dashboards, funnels, feature flags, session replay, surveys, or a settings UI. Use ClickHouse, SQL, notebooks, BI tools, or agentic analytics on top of the tables."},"16":{"id":"/-14","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#why-build-this","content":"If your analytics events already need to end up in ClickHouse, a traditional product analytics pipeline can become a detour: send events to a vendor, let the vendor store them in its managed backend, then export them back through S3 into your own ClickHouse warehouse."},"17":{"id":"/-15","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#why-build-this","content":"This project removes that loop. It gives you the first-party capture layer and ingest service needed to send product events directly into ClickHouse, while leaving analysis and visualization to the SQL, BI, notebook, and agentic tools you already use on top of the warehouse."},"18":{"id":"/-16","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#start","content":"Sending events: browser SDK, backend/direct API, batch API, gzip, and event naming examples."},"19":{"id":"/-17","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#start","content":"Identifying users: anonymous IDs, `identify`, `$set`, `$set_once`, aliases, reset, and query implications."},"20":{"id":"/-18","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#start","content":"React usage: provider, hook, and viewport tracking setup for React and Next.js."},"21":{"id":"/-19","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#operate","content":"Architecture: system boundaries, event flow, identity flow, and how the pieces fit together."},"22":{"id":"/-20","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#operate","content":"ClickHouse schema: table/view schemas, JSON property access, and query patterns for humans and agents."},"23":{"id":"/-21","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#deployment","content":"Docker Compose: local stack, ClickHouse Cloud connection details, production container model, environment variables, and migration workflow."},"24":{"id":"/-22","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","u