, ports, health checks, and migration-on-start behavior as the default stack, but replaces the GHCR ingest image with `build.context: .` and `packages/ingest-service/Dockerfile`."},"65":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-20","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#production-shape","content":"Run the ingest service as a container close to ClickHouse. Put it behind a TLS-terminating reverse proxy or load balancer. Browser applications talk to the public HTTPS ingest URL. Backend services can use the same public URL or a private network URL."},"66":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-21","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#production-shape","content":"Recommended production model:"},"67":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-22","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#production-shape","content":"one or more ingest service containers,"},"68":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-23","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#production-shape","content":"shared ClickHouse database on a supported stable or LTS ClickHouse release,"},"69":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-24","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#production-shape","content":"stable `PUBLIC_API_KEYS` when backend or no-origin requests are used,"},"70":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-25","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#production-shape","content":"explicit `ALLOWED_ORIGINS`,"},"71":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-26","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#production-shape","content":"`LOG_LEVEL=warn` or stricter for high-volume traffic,"},"72":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-27","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#production-shape","content":"migrations run manually before deploy,"},"73":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-28","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#production-shape","content":"`MIGRATE_ON_START=false` or omitted in production."},"74":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-29","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#production-shape","content":"The ingest service does not require Redis, Postgres, Kafka, object storage, or a background worker."},"75":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-30","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#container-image","content":"The published ingest service image is:"},"76":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-31","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#container-image","content":"Use the `sha-<commit>` tag for production rollouts, or the image digest reported by GHCR after the publish job completes. The mutable `latest` tag is useful for quick trials but should not be the rollout target for a stable environment. For the strictest rollout, deploy `ghcr.io/marcklingen/clickhouse-product-analytics/ingest-service@sha256:<digest>`."},"77":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-32","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#clickhouse-cloud","content":"ClickHouse Cloud works with the same ingest service configuration. The service uses the official `@clickhouse/client` package and passes `CLICKHOUSE_URL`, `CLICKHOUSE_USER`, `CLICKHOUSE_PASSWORD`, and `CLICKHOUSE_DATABASE` directly to the client. No code change is required for a Cloud service as long as the URL is the HTTPS endpoint for the ClickHouse HTTP interface."},"78":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-33","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#clickhouse-cloud","content":"Use the connection details from the ClickHouse Cloud service connection menu. For the Node.js or HTTPS connection form, the URL usually has this shape:"},"79":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-34","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#clickhouse-cloud","content":"Then configure the ingest service the same way you would for a self-hosted production deployment:"},"80":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-35","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#clickhouse-cloud","content":"Run migrations from a trusted environment that can reach the ClickHouse Cloud service:"},"81":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-36","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#clickhouse-cloud","content":"The browser SDK and React package do not connect to ClickHouse Cloud directly. They should continue to send events to the ingest service `apiHost`; the ingest service is the only component that needs ClickHouse Cloud credentials."},"82":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-37","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#environment-variables","content":"Variable"},"83":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-38","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#environment-variables","content":"Required"},"84":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-39","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#environment-variables","content":"Default"},"85":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-40","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#environment-variables","content":"Purpose"},"86":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-41","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","